{"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week number for the week containing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"datetime"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The ISO 8601 week number is the same for every day of the week (from"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Moday through Sunday).  That can produce some unusual results"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(described below)."}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"property","extendedModule":"GLib","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"weekOfYear"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"title":"weekOfYear","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","externalID":"s:4GLib16DateTimeProtocolPAAE10weekOfYearSivp::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib8DateTimeC"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/datetime\/weekofyear"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"weekOfYear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The first week of the year is week 1.  This is the week that contains"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the first Thursday of the year.  Equivalently, this is the first week","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that has more than 4 of its days falling within the calendar year.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The value 0 is never returned by this function.  Days contained"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"within a year but occurring before the first ISO 8601 week of that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"year are considered as being contained in the last week of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"previous year.  Similarly, the final days of a calendar year may be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"considered as being part of the first ISO 8601 week of the next year"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"if 4 or more days of that week are contained within the new year.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/weekOfYear"},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTime":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDateTime"},{"type":"text","text":" is a structure that combines a Gregorian date and time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into a single structure."}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DateTime","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"DateTime","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DateTime","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetime"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTime/weekOfYear":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/weekOfYear","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week number for the week containing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"datetime"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The ISO 8601 week number is the same for every day of the week (from"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Moday through Sunday).  That can produce some unusual results"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(described below).","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"weekOfYear"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetime\/weekofyear","title":"weekOfYear"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTime/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations":{"role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetime\/datetimeprotocol-implementations","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"DateTimeProtocol Implementations"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"}}}